ALFONSO ΓÇö THE SYNTHESIS PUSHING THROUGH (Mandatory)
Alfonso carries the Jagged Crown of Namira and a body infused with Peryite's blessing. Hjolmar said "two songs fighting." But Hjolmar was wrong about one thing ΓÇö Namira and Peryite aren't fighting each other. They're trying to MERGE. The dissonance isn't conflict between the patrons. It's the pressure of two divine frequencies trying to harmonize through a mortal body that wasn't built for it.
Read aloud (to Alfonso's player):
"You're walking when something happens in your chest. Not pain. Not nausea. Something you have no name for. The Jagged Crown ΓÇö which has never done anything like this before ΓÇö SPIKES. A pulse of heat from the dragon bone on your skull that drops into your stomach and spreads outward. Your teeth ache. Your tongue tastes copper.
And then the hunger hits. Not for food ΓÇö the Crown burned that out of you permanently. This is hunger for SOMETHING ELSE. Purpose. Direction. Movement. The Crown wants to consume and the plague in your blood wants to spread and for one disorienting second they're both pulling you the same way and you can almost see what that direction IS ΓÇö
Then it's gone. Like a word on the tip of your tongue that dissolved before you could say it.
